Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers
MANILA , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading Philippine newspapers Monday .
Manila Bulletin :
-- Philippine President Joseph Estrada has authorized the National Development Corp. to issue 50 billion pesos ( 1.25 billion U.S. dollars ) of long-term bonds to tap the support of private banks in modernizing the agriculture sector .
Manila Standard :
-- President Estrada has indicated that he wants to keep his cabinet intact amid speculations that a shake-up is imminent to reinvigorate his administration after its first six months .
Philippine Inquirer :
-- The Moro Islamic Liberation Front vowed Sunday to pursue its fight for an independent Islamic state in Mindanao despite a call from President Estrada for a peace accord next year .
Business World :
-- The Philippine Central Bank expects this year 's inflation based on 1988 price levels to average at 9 percent , or lower than its commitment with the International Monetary Fund .
